				<div id="bodyContent" class="vector-body" aria-labelledby="firstHeading" data-mw-ve-target-container>
					<div class="vector-body-before-content">
							<div class="mw-indicators">
		</div>

						<div id="siteSub" class="noprint">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>
					</div>
					<div id="contentSub"><div id="mw-content-subtitle"></div></div>
					
					
					<div id="mw-content-text" class="mw-body-content"><div class="mw-content-ltr mw-parser-output" lang="en" dir="ltr"><figure class="mw-halign-right" typeof="mw:File/Thumb"><a href="/wiki/File:Church_in_Wales_flag.svg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a5/Church_in_Wales_flag.svg/200px-Church_in_Wales_flag.svg.png" decoding="async" width="200" height="100" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a5/Church_in_Wales_flag.svg/300px-Church_in_Wales_flag.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a5/Church_in_Wales_flag.svg/400px-Church_in_Wales_flag.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="894" data-file-height="447" /></a><figcaption>The Flag of the Church in Wales</figcaption></figure>
<p>The <b>Flag of the Church in Wales</b> is the flag used to represent the <a href="/wiki/Church_in_Wales" title="Church in Wales">Church in Wales</a>. It consists of a blue cross on a white background with a gold <a href="/wiki/Celtic_cross" title="Celtic cross">celtic cross</a> in the centre. It was adopted in 1954 by the <a href="/wiki/Governing_Body_of_the_Church_in_Wales" title="Governing Body of the Church in Wales">Governing Body of the Church in Wales</a>.
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="History">History</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Flag_of_the_Church_in_Wales&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: History"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<figure class="mw-halign-left" typeof="mw:File/Thumb"><a href="/wiki/File:Flag_of_Saint_David(early).svg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7c/Flag_of_Saint_David%28early%29.svg/100px-Flag_of_Saint_David%28early%29.svg.png" decoding="async" width="100" height="67" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7c/Flag_of_Saint_David%28early%29.svg/150px-Flag_of_Saint_David%28early%29.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7c/Flag_of_Saint_David%28early%29.svg/200px-Flag_of_Saint_David%28early%29.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="1620" data-file-height="1080" /></a><figcaption>The unofficial flag between 1920 and 1954</figcaption></figure>
<p>Prior to <a href="/wiki/Welsh_Church_Act_1914" title="Welsh Church Act 1914">its disestablishment in 1920</a>, the <a href="/wiki/Anglican_Church" class="mw-redirect" title="Anglican Church">Anglican Church</a> in Wales was a part of the <a href="/wiki/Church_of_England" title="Church of England">Church of England</a>. The flag used to represent the church was the <a href="/wiki/Saint_George%27s_Cross" title="Saint George&#39;s Cross">Saint George's Cross</a>, the same as the Church of England. Following the <a href="/wiki/Welsh_Church_Act_1914" title="Welsh Church Act 1914">Welsh Church Act 1914</a>, the Church in Wales was disestablished and separated from the Church of England. In the 1930s, the Church of England started to fly <a href="/wiki/Flag_of_England" title="Flag of England">flags of England</a> with the coat of arms of the respective <a href="/wiki/Diocese" title="Diocese">diocese</a> in the upper left of the flag. This practice became popular and was adopted by the Church in Wales unofficially using a <a href="/wiki/Flag_of_Saint_David" title="Flag of Saint David">flag of Saint David</a> with the colours reversed in place of the Saint George's Cross.<sup id="cite_ref-bbc_1-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-bbc-1">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>
</p><p>In 1954 the Church in Wales' governing body passed a motion for an official flag to represent the church. Following negotiations with the <a href="/wiki/College_of_Arms" title="College of Arms">College of Arms</a>, it was decided that the new flag would consist of a blue cross with a white background with a gold celtic cross in the centre.<sup id="cite_ref-bbc_1-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-bbc-1">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> The flag gained official status on 9 December 1954.<sup id="cite_ref-bbc_1-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-bbc-1">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Official_heraldry">Official heraldry</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Flag_of_the_Church_in_Wales&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2" title="Edit section: Official heraldry"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p>The official grant of arms defines the flag as "Argent, on a Cross Azure a Celtic Cross Or". There have been differences in the celtic cross in the flag with versions where the cross has the spaces within it filled with gold rather than showing the blue of the cross.<sup id="cite_ref-crw_2-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-crw-2">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> As a flag for the Welsh made separate from England, the flag of the Church in Wales is viewed as a uniquely Welsh flag.<sup id="cite_ref-fi_3-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-fi-3">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> Churches can use the flag, or the flag of their diocese.<sup id="cite_ref-fi_3-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-fi-3">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="References">References</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Flag_of_the_Church_in_Wales&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3" title="Edit section: References"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
